@startuml Time-Limited Policy Expiry
title **Contract Policy: Time Limit Enforcement**\nWhat happens when a contract's time window expires

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #424242
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #9E9E9E
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #E8F5E9

actor "Dr. Martinez\n(Point Blue)" as Researcher #E8F5E9
participant "Point Blue\nEDC Connector" as PB_EDC #E3F2FD
participant "Caney Fork\nEDC Connector" as CF_EDC #E8F5E9

== July 2026: Within prototype phase ==

note over PB_EDC, CF_EDC
  Current date: **2026-07-15**
  Policy expiry: **2026-09-30**
end note

Researcher -> PB_EDC : Negotiate contract for SOC data\npurpose = "AgronomicModelTraining"
PB_EDC -> CF_EDC : Contract negotiation

group Contract Policy: time-limited
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : dateTime <= 2026-09-30 ?\n2026-07-15 <= 2026-09-30 => **YES**
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : purpose check => **YES**
end

CF_EDC --> PB_EDC : Contract FINALIZED
PB_EDC --> Researcher : Contract active, transfer available

Researcher -> PB_EDC : Transfer data
PB_EDC -> CF_EDC : DSP Transfer
CF_EDC --> PB_EDC : SOC dataset delivered

note over Researcher
  Dr. Martinez receives the data and
  begins model training during the
  active prototype phase.
end note

== October 2026: Prototype phase ended ==

/ note over PB_EDC, CF_EDC
  Current date: **2026-10-15**
  Policy expiry: **2026-09-30** (passed)
end note

Researcher -> PB_EDC : Request new contract for\nupdated SOC measurements
PB_EDC -> CF_EDC : Contract negotiation

group Contract Policy: time-limited #FFEBEE
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : dateTime <= 2026-09-30 ?\n2026-10-15 > 2026-09-30 => **NO**
  note right of CF_EDC #FFCDD2
    Time constraint no longer satisfied.
    => **NEGOTIATION REJECTED**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> PB_EDC : Contract TERMINATED\n(time constraint expired)
PB_EDC --> Researcher : Negotiation failed: offer expired

note over Researcher
  **What this means for Dr. Martinez:**

  - The **existing contract** from July is
    still valid for data already transferred
    (EDC doesn't revoke past transfers)
  - **New contracts** cannot be negotiated
    until the provider updates the policy
    with a new expiry date
  - This is a **natural consent renewal point**:
    Caney Fork decides whether to extend
    sharing into the next project phase

  **What Caney Fork should do:**
  - Review the partnership at the end of
    the prototype phase
  - If satisfied, publish a new policy
    with updated expiry (e.g., 2027-09-30)
  - If not, simply leave the expired policy
    - no new access is possible
end note

== Renewal (if agreed) ==

CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : Provider updates policy:\ndateTime <= **2027-09-30**
note right of CF_EDC
  New policy created for the
  next project phase, potentially
  with updated terms (different
  purposes, new obligations, etc.)
end note

Researcher -> PB_EDC : Negotiate new contract
PB_EDC -> CF_EDC : Contract negotiation
CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : dateTime <= 2027-09-30 ? **YES**
CF_EDC --> PB_EDC : Contract FINALIZED
PB_EDC --> Researcher : New contract active

@enduml
